Gather has specified grouping. Eg every 3 make a group.
Group on the other hand resorts in a corner turn.
In this graph we just combine outside the scatter box to bring all data together correctly
We have used the `to archive' step to provide the calibration tables to the next dependent task
The DQA loops are not perfect. We can not loop back into invert. Also they have a fixed no of cycles before finishing. These cycles would not have anything to do, if it has converged
